.TH "ep_loop_check_proc" 9 "ep_loop_check_proc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ep_loop_check_proc \- verify that adding an epoll file inside another epoll structure, does not violate the constraints, in terms of closed loops, or too deep chains (which can result in excessive stack usage).
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ep_loop_check_proc
.BI "(struct eventpoll *ep "  ","
.BI "int depth "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "depth" 12
Current depth of the path being checked.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns zero if adding the epoll \fIfile\fP inside current epoll
structure \fIep\fP does not violate the constraints, or -1 otherwise.
